@node INTRODUZIONE "Introduction"

    This two utilities create a specific number of files from a bigger file . They are very simple to use.
        - select the souce
        - set how to split
        - click on slink
        - pray... ;-)
        - no Header is written
        - files can be joined with the program Join (part of AmigaDos®).

    With @{b}Master@{ub} you can split a file in two different ways:
    - how many files
    - how many bytes must be a single file

    With @{b}SubSlink@{ub} you can save only specified parts of a file.  You've to set the starting and ending bytes of the file that will be created. You can do this using only 4 files  Be carefull that @{b}the first byte of the source is 0 and NOT 1 ! ! ! !@{ub} .
    So, if you want to save a file (1024 bytes long) in two equal parts:
    - first subfile Startbyte=0 and Endbyte=512
    - second subfile Startbyte=512 and Endbytes=1024
    = you'll obtain 2 files 512 bytes long with the names you've set
@endnode
